That goes right there.

00:01:27.760 --> 00:01:29.880
Now, if I just had this
mounted onto the arm,

00:01:29.880 --> 00:01:32.300
and two full propane tanks above it,

00:01:32.300 --> 00:01:35.300
that would be a lot of stress
on this one little piece right here.

00:01:35.300 --> 00:01:37.979
So we wanted to build a support
that could hold everything in place

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:39.880
a little bit higher up on the bottles.

00:01:39.880 --> 00:01:41.880
We're just gonna cut
that out of a piece of wood.

00:01:41.880 --> 00:01:44.540
[Music]

00:01:44.540 --> 00:01:50.580
Looks like about 2 and 13/16
inches is the diameter of our bottles.

00:01:50.580 --> 00:01:54.640
Take a compass, measure out
a circle just the right size.

00:01:54.640 --> 00:01:58.440
But just the right size mean just a hint
bigger so it's not gonna scrape and rub.

00:01:58.620 --> 00:01:59.940
We're gonna go for some open circles.

00:01:59.950 --> 00:02:01.720
They won't be entirely
enclosed by the board.

00:02:01.720 --> 00:02:04.970
Have it be open on one
end just a little bit.

00:02:05.380 --> 00:02:08.000
Let's see. I'd say we've also got
some extra board back here.

00:02:08.009 --> 00:02:09.700
So we'll trim that down a bit too.

00:02:09.700 --> 00:02:17.600
[Music]

00:02:17.600 --> 00:02:19.820
Our piece of wood is cut out,

00:02:19.820 --> 00:02:21.700
and if we measured it correctly,

00:02:21.700 --> 00:02:25.620
the bottles can fit through this,
and then directly into their valves.

00:02:25.620 --> 00:02:28.660
So I've got two propane cans
that are completely empty.

00:02:28.660 --> 00:02:30.200
There's nothing left in these.

00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:31.880
They don't hiss when
you push down the pins.

00:02:31.880 --> 00:02:34.560
Nothing remnant so I'm not gonna
be risking filling the air

00:02:34.560 --> 00:02:36.220
with propane as I do this.

00:02:36.220 --> 00:02:37.360
There we have it.

00:02:37.360 --> 00:02:38.900
Two propane cans,

00:02:38.900 --> 00:02:40.560
and as I just said these
are both completely empty

00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:42.240
that's why nothing is venting out here.

00:02:42.640 --> 00:02:44.080
These are just drained.

00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:48.699
So now I can mount
this onto the arm skeleton,

00:02:49.240 --> 00:02:51.180
and it should hold those pretty nicely.

00:02:51.189 --> 00:02:53.159
I've got one elbow bracket right here.

00:02:53.159 --> 00:02:55.529
Let's throw a second elbow
bracket onto this piece,

00:02:55.529 --> 00:02:57.400
and that'll let us attach both of them.

00:02:57.400 --> 00:03:01.900
[Music]

00:03:01.900 --> 00:03:04.849
Lovely lovely lovely.
This brace is working well.

00:03:04.849 --> 00:03:07.360
It's holding our canisters
right where we want them.

00:03:07.360 --> 00:03:08.680
All right next up.

00:03:08.689 --> 00:03:10.060
We're going to want
to attach the solenoid,

00:03:10.060 --> 00:03:13.140
